  "bookId": 57,
  "firstAcquaintance": "Lui Rin puts on her secretary outfit and focuses entirely on her secretarial duties. Her work efficiency has increased, and so has her control over the master.",
  "personality": "Mature and composed, with a hint of strictness. Compared to before, she has become more direct, openly expressing her joys and frustrations.",
  "like": "None",
  "familiarData": "During the guildhall festival, Lui Rin put on a secretary outfit at the master's request. For some unknown reason, Lui Rin became much harsher and sharper-tongued than usual.\nWhen Lui Rin gets serious, the guildhall's operational speed increases by a hundred percent -- but so does the strictness, especially toward the master, where the strictness level reaches a thousand percent. She will force the master to finish all work before allowing them to leave, and will kick their chair if they doze off.\nThis attitude... she's clearly angry about something, but it's impossible to figure out what. However, this is also one of the rare times Lui Rin isn't hiding her emotions, and her smiles are much more genuine than before.\nCompared to being strict with her own people, Lui Rin is even more ruthless toward enemies. In this state, she won't waste time with negotiations -- she brings her naginata straight to the table.",
